  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the programme is to contribute to poverty reduction by strengthening financial, administrative and decentralised governance.
The program has three components:

1. General budget support to co-finance the poverty strategy, as well as support for public financial management, public procurement reforms and monitoring and evaluation of the poverty strategy;
2. Support for administrative reforms;
3. Support for decentralisation.

On the basis of a UFT review in May 2011, which took place following the decision on phasing out the aid cooperation between Denmark and Benin, support for public reforms and general budget support has been completed by the end of 2011.

At the end of 2012, the remaining activities related to the following will be completed:

(i) public procurement procedures;
(ii) public financial management;
(iii) monitoring and evaluation of the poverty strategy; 
(iv) decentralisation (delegated partnership with Germany)</narrative>
  </description>
